# How to start git with 'git clone'

1. Create remote repository on github.com
2. Click Code button and copy to paste button.
3. $ git clone { github repo addr } on your terminal.
4. Do you work.
5. $ git add {filename} -> $ git commit -> $ git push origin main

##Special Features

### Conventional Commits

[Reference] (https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/)

- feat: features
- docs: documentation
- conf: configuration
- fix: bug-fix
- ci: continuous integration
- test: test codes
- hot-fix: hot-fix
- refactor: refactoring
